      "content": "East Asian Humanities Major Articulation Information The East Asian Humanities major is a comparative study of East Asian cultures. The curriculum seeks to prepare students for cross-regional comparative work, emphasizing cultural and literary analysis, media studies, and interdisciplinary humanities. The major offers a high degree of flexibility, allowing students to draw coursework from two or more national traditions in East Asia (China, Japan, and South Korea, among others) and covering both the modern and classical periods. Students must complete 8 courses (or 40 units), and while we recommend acquiring a reading knowledge of at least one foreign language, the major can be entirely completed through English-taught courses. Coursework for requirements can be completed upon transfer to UC Berkeley. Students intending the major should enroll in at least one of the following classes in their first semester, along with upper-division courses from the list provided on our website or the Berkeley Catalog . BUDDSTD/EALANG C 50 Introduction to Buddhism Chinese 7A Introduction to Modern Chinese Literature and Culture Chinese 7B Introduction to Pre-modern Chinese Literature and Culture Japanese 7A Introduction to Modern Japanese Literature and Culture Japanese 7B Introduction to Modern Pre-modern Literature and Culture Korean 7A Introduction to Modern Korean Literature and Culture Korean 7B Introduction to Pre-modern Chinese Literature and Culture Advising: Students with questions about transferring into the major in East Asian Humanities are encouraged to contact our undergraduate major advisor(UMA): Cassandra Dunn Department Website: http://ealc.berkeley.edu/ Email: cassandrajj@berkeley.edu Appointments: Schedule an appointment (in-person or remotely ).",
      "contentHtml": "<p class=\"ql-align-center\"><strong>East Asian Humanities Major Articulation Information</strong></p><p><br></p><p><br></p><p>The <strong>East Asian Humanities</strong> major is a comparative study of East Asian cultures.&nbsp;The curriculum seeks to prepare students for cross-regional comparative work, emphasizing cultural and literary analysis, media studies, and interdisciplinary humanities.</p><p><br></p><p>The major offers a high degree of flexibility, allowing students to draw coursework from two or more national traditions in East Asia (China, Japan, and South Korea, among others) and covering both the modern and classical periods.&nbsp;Students must complete 8 courses (or 40 units), and while we recommend acquiring a reading knowledge of at least one foreign language, the major can be entirely completed through English-taught courses.</p><p><br></p><p>Coursework for requirements can be completed upon transfer to UC Berkeley. Students intending the major should enroll in at least one of the following classes in their first semester, along with upper-division courses from the list provided on <a href=\"https://ealc.berkeley.edu/content/east-asian-humanities-major-requirements\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">our website</a> or the <a href=\"https://undergraduate.catalog.berkeley.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Berkeley Catalog</a>.</p><p><br></p><ul><li>BUDDSTD/EALANG C 50 Introduction to Buddhism</li><li>Chinese 7A Introduction to Modern Chinese Literature and Culture</li><li>Chinese 7B Introduction to Pre-modern Chinese Literature and Culture</li><li>Japanese 7A Introduction to Modern Japanese Literature and Culture</li><li>Japanese 7B Introduction to Modern Pre-modern Literature and Culture</li><li>Korean 7A Introduction to Modern Korean Literature and Culture</li><li>Korean 7B Introduction to Pre-modern Chinese Literature and Culture</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>Advising:</strong></p><p>Students with questions about transferring into the major in East Asian Humanities are encouraged to contact our undergraduate major advisor(UMA):</p><p>Cassandra Dunn</p><p>Department Website: <a href=\"http://ealc.berkeley.edu/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">http://ealc.berkeley.edu/</a></p><p>Email: <a href=\"mailto:cassandrajj@berkeley.edu\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">cassandrajj@berkeley.edu</a></p><p>Appointments: <a href=\"https://calendly.com/cassandra-dunn-ug-advisor\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\">Schedule an appointment (in-person or remotely</a>).</p>"
